description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cygnet Heathers, Grout Street, West Bromwich, B70 0HD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£8.50 - £8.80 p/h&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cygnet Health Care you’ll have the chance to make a real impact on patients and their families. You’ll be exposed to all kinds of new challenges and responsibilities, to ensure you continue learning and developing as you go.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Therapy Coordinatorfor our site Cygnet Heathers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you’ll:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deliver planned activities for patients under the direction of Occupational Therapy department and Multidisciplinary Team&lt;br /&gt;Contribute ideas, create and facilitate events and activities safely and support people to structure their time through meaningful activity&lt;br /&gt;Have involvement in the delivery of one to one and group interventions&lt;br /&gt;Implement individual care plans during activity sessions and take into account specific interests and opportunities to promote choice and independence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We&#39;re looking for people who have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good understanding of mental health diagnosis&lt;br /&gt;Knowledge of recovery approaches and social inclusion is desirable&lt;br /&gt;Experience of supporting service users with mental illness&lt;br /&gt;A relevant healthcare qualification is desirable&lt;br /&gt;Effective communication skills, good organisations skills and a positive attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we’ll offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Increased hourly rate following successful completion of probation&lt;br /&gt;Company pension scheme&lt;br /&gt;Regular supervision from a qualified Occupational Therapist&lt;br /&gt;Opportunities for CPD, training, development and research&lt;br /&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 40hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Set Rota - 12 hour shifts. 3 one week and 4 the next week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
